headline: The 12 Best Stocks of 2025—and 3 That Could Be Set for a Fall
summary: Barron’s took a look at the year’s hottest stocks to see if investors should be worried.  About 60% of S&P 500 stocks are up this year, and the average gain for shares was about 10%.  A handful of S&P 500 stocks have done much better.

headline: Could Intel’s Apple Chip Ambitions and Malaysia Bet Redefine Its Foundry Narrative (INTC)?
summary: In recent days, reports have suggested that Intel could manufacture Apple’s M-series chips on its 18A process as early as 2027, alongside a planned US$208 million expansion of its packaging and testing operations in Malaysia to bolster supply resilience. Beyond the immediate headlines, the prospect of Apple as a foundry customer and the Malaysia investment both act as real-world tests of Intel’s effort to reposition itself as a competitive, globally diversified contract chip...
